Google Will Pay $500 Million to Settle Federal Probe Over Online Drug Ads

-- B y   S a r a   F o r d e n
-- 
2011-08-24T15:20:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/google-will-pay-500-million-to-settle-federal-probe-over-online-drug-ads.html
Google Inc. (GOOG)  agreed to pay $500
million to settle U.S. allegations that it allowed online
Canadian pharmacies to place advertising resulting in the
illegal importation of drugs, the  Justice Department  said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sara Forden in Washington at 
 sforden@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Fred Strasser at 
 fstrasser@bloomberg.net  